	('HDI/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer', 'A spherical polymer that provides a soft-focus effect and enhances product feel.', '1', null),
	('Neopentyl Glycol Diheptanoate', 'An emollient that improves product spreadability and leaves a smooth, non-greasy finish.', '1', null),
	('Sodium Stearoyl Glutamate', 'Sodium stearoyl glutamate is a hypoallergenic, amino acid-based emulsifier that helps to blend the oil and water together in a cosmetic formulation. It helps to condition the skin and the hair. It also acts as a surfactant in higher amounts. It’s sodium part makes it an amino acid salt and it is non-irritating in nature. It is considered as natural, and environmentally friendly.', '1', '2'),
	('Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate', 'A plant-derived emulsifier commonly used to stabilize oil-in-water formulations, providing a smooth and consistent texture.', '1', null),
	('Decyl Glucoside', 'Decyl glucoside is a non-ionic surfactant that is used as a foaming, cleansing, conditioning, or emulsifying agent. It can be used as a base surfactant or a co-surfactant in cleansers. It has excellent foaming capacity and good dermatological compatibility. It can be used alongside other glucosides to enhance the foam and skin conditioning properties. It can also be used in ionic formulations to add foam depth and emulsifying properties.', '2', '3'),
	('Disteardimonium Hectorite', 'Disteardimonium Hectorite, a naturally occurring clay mineral hectorite is a thickening agent for cosmetic ingredients. It is used in face and skin creams, as well as deodorants, foundations and lipsticks.', '1', null),
	('Sorbitan Isostearate', 'An emulsifier derived from plant-based sorbitol and isostearic acid, used to blend oil and water in formulations while providing a smooth texture.', '1', '3'),
	('Aluminum Hydroxide', 'A stabilizing and opacifying agent that helps prevent the formulation from breaking down and provides a smooth texture.', '1', '3'),
	('Sorbitan Oleate', 'Acts as an emulsifier and skin conditioning agent, promoting hydration and helping the skin retain moisture while enhancing the smoothness of the skin’s surface.', '1', '3'),
	('3-O-Ethyl Ascorbic Acid', 'A stable derivative of Vitamin C known for its brightening and antioxidant properties. It helps to reduce the appearance of dark spots and hyperpigmentation while also improving the skin’s overall texture and promoting a radiant complexion.', '1', '2'),
	('Himanthalia Elongata Extract', 'A type of brown algae extract known for its rich content of antioxidants, minerals, and vitamins. It helps to hydrate and protect the skin, providing nourishment and promoting skin elasticity. It is often used in skincare for its anti-aging and moisturizing benefits.', '3', '2'),
	('Biosaccharide Gum-4', 'It helps to retain moisture in the skin, providing long-lasting hydration and creating a protective barrier. It is commonly used in skincare for sensitive skin, offering relief from irritation and enhancing skin softness.', '1', null),
	('Fragrance', 'Adds a pleasant scent to the product, enhancing the user experience. It is a blend of natural and/or synthetic aromatic compounds.', null, null),
	('Hexamidine Diisethionate', 'Hexamidine Diisethionate helps cleanse the skin or prevent odor by destroying or inhibiting the growth of microorganisms.', '1', '2'),
	('Lauryl Glucoside', 'It is gentle on the skin, making it suitable for sensitive skin types. Lauryl Glucoside helps to remove dirt, oil, and impurities without stripping the skin is natural moisture, and it enhances the overall texture of the product.', '2', '3'),
	('Sodium Lauroyl Methyl Isethionate', 'Sodium lauroyl methyl isethionate is the chemical name for the sodium salt of the methyl lauric acid ester of isethionic acid. It serves as a surfactant and cleaning agent in cosmetics and personal care items. It is a very gentle cleaning agent with rich, luxurious foam and a refined after-feel. Additionally, it is very well soluble in water, making it rinsable. It is an alternative to a more widely known surfactant, sodium cocoyl isethionate. As a raw material, sodium lauroyl methyl isethionate is often available as white-to-off-white flakes or chips', '1', '2'),
	('Sodium Cocoyl Glutamate', 'It is a cleansing agent and a good emulsifier that leaves the skin gentler, cleaner, conditioned and smoother without being too harsh. This ingredient is effective for sensitive or oily skin types.', '1', '3'),
	('Sodium Methyl Oleoyl Taurate', 'Sodium Methyl Oleoyl Taurate is a sodium salt of the oleic acid amide of N-methyl taurine.', '1', '4'),
	('NaCI', 'NaCl, or Sodium Chloride, is commonly used in facial skincare as a thickening agent, preservative, and humectant. It helps adjust the texture of products, extends shelf life, and retains moisture in the skin by attracting water. While not a key active ingredient, it plays an essential role in product', null, null),
	('Ethylhexylglycerin', 'Ethylhexylglycerin is a skin softening agent that offers multiple benefits for skin care and cosmetic products. It acts as a humectant and hydrates skin and hair deeply without leaving them heavy or sticky. Ethylhexylglycerin is also a preservative that increases the shelf life of a wide variety of products.', '2', '2'),
	('PEG-150 Distearate', 'PEG Distearate ingredients clean the skin and hair by helping water to mix with oil and dirt so that they can be rinsed away. They also help to form emulsions by reducing the surface tension of the substances to be emulsified and help other ingredients to dissolve in a solvent in which they would not normally dissolve.', '2', '3'),
	('Niacinamide', 'Niacinamide (also called nicotinamide) is a form of vitamin B-3, and not only does it protect the skin from environmental damage, but it also helps build proteins for healthier skin. The benefits offered by this ingredient are massive, and one can depend on it for skin rejuvenation and protection.', '1', '4'),
	('Chondrus Crispus (Carrageenan) Extract', 'Chondrus Crispus extract is rich in vitamins and minerals, offering skin-nourishing benefits. It is often used in formulations aimed at sensitive skin, as it is gentle and non-irritating.', '1', '3'),
	('Panthenol', 'It is used as a moisturizer and humectant in cosmetics and personal care products.', '1', '2'),
	('Calendula Officinalis Flower Extract', 'Calendula Officinalis Flower Extract is a healing and anti-aging ingredient widely used in personal care products. It is rich in flavonoids that give the extract its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.', '1', '2'),
	('Ethoxydiglycol', 'Ethoxydiglycol is a solubilizer, solvent, humectant, moisturizer, and perfuming agent widely used in cosmetics and personal care products.', '5', '4'),
	('Sodium PCA', 'It is a natural ingredient that looks like salt. Sodium PCA is a humectant that draws moisture to the other layers of the surface and helps the skin and hair retain moisture, resulting in a youthful appearance. The full form of Sodium PCA is sodium pyrrolidone carboxylic acid.', '1', '2'),
	('Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract', 'ts antioxidant potential may protect the skin from the harmful UV rays that cause sunburn and premature aging. It also soothes dry skin. Topical application of this extract reduces the scaling of the skin and improves its elasticity and hydration. It can be used as an anti-cellulite agent due to its caffeine content.', '2', '4'),
	('Salicylic Acid', 'Salicylic acid is a crystalline phenolic acid C7H6O3 that is used medicinally especially as a skin exfoliant and in the form of salts and other derivatives as an analgesic and antipyretic', '8', '2'),
	('Peumus Boldus Leaf Extract', 'It is often used in skincare for its ability to soothe irritated skin, reduce redness, and promote a healthy complexion. Peumus Boldus Leaf Extract is also believed to help with detoxification and has been traditionally used to support skin healing. It’s typically found in formulations targeting sensitive or acne-prone skin due to its calming and purifying effects.', '1', '2'),
	('Pentylene Glycol', 'It helps to retain moisture in the skin by drawing water from the environment and preventing water loss. In addition to its moisturizing properties, Pentylene Glycol also has antimicrobial benefits, which can help improve the shelf life of products. It enhances the texture and stability of formulations and can also improve the absorption of other active ingredients. It is widely used in a variety of skincare products, such as moisturizers, serums, and cleansers.', '1', '2'),
	('Ceramide NP', 'It helps improve the look and feel of dry or dehydrated skin thanks to its water retention properties. It also reinforces skin’s barrier strength, so it better resists external stressors and thus contributes to supple, resilient, hydrated skin overall.', '1', '2'),
	('Ethylhexyl Palmitate', 'It softens and smoothens the skin. It reduces moisture loss from the upper layers and improves the look of the skin. As a solvent, it helps solubilize other ingredients, helping active ingredients more readily penetrate into the skin. It helps active ingredients such as avobenzone and ethylhexyl triazone, commonly found in sunscreen, disperse and remain evenly suspended in a formula.', '1', '3'),
	('Cetyl Ethylhexanoate', 'Cetyl ethylhexanoate is abilities as an emollient enable it to maintain the skin moisture levels as a bonus benefit to enhancing texture and sensory feel.', '1', '4'),
	('Polyglyceryl-3 Cocoate', 'Polyglyceryl-3 Cocoate is a plant-derived emulsifier and surfactant from coconut oil. It helps mix oil and water, gently cleanses, hydrates, and conditions the skin. Mild, eco-friendly, and suitable for sensitive skin, it is commonly used in cleansers, creams, and baby care products.', '1', '2'),
	('Trihydroxystearin', 'It is a popular ingredient in skin care products because of its emollient and moisturizing properties. It helps to hydrate and soften the skin, making it smoother and more supple. Trihydroxystearin is also used as a thickener in creams and lotions, helping to improve their texture and consistency.', '1', '2'),
	('Glyceryl Behenate', 'Glyceryl Behenate is an emulsifier and thickener that stabilizes formulations, enhances texture, and leaves skin feeling smooth and soft. Commonly used in creams, lotions, and balms.', '3', '2'),
	('Polyglyceryl-6 Octastearate', 'Polyglyceryl-6 Octastearate is a plant-based emulsifier that blends oil and water, stabilizes formulations, and provides a smooth, non-greasy feel. Common in creams, lotions, and sunscreens.', '1', '2'),
	('Olea Europaea (Olive) Fruit Oil', 'Olea Europaea (Olive) Fruit Oil is a natural oil rich in antioxidants and fatty acids. It moisturizes, nourishes, and protects the skin, making it soft and smooth. Commonly used in creams, lotions, and cleansers.', null, null),
	('Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Extract', 'It also protects the skin from harmful environmental factors. Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Extract isn’t new to the cosmetic industry and has been used for centuries due to its magical properties.', '1', '2'),
	('Canola Oil', 'The oil key components include unsaturated fatty acids, such as oleic, linoleic, and alpha-linolenic acids, which nourish and hydrate the skin, making it suitable for moisturizers, serums, and hair care products.', '1', '3'),
	('Ceteareth-25', 'Ceteareth-25 is an emulsifier and surfactant that helps blend oil and water, creating stable and smooth formulations. It’s commonly used in creams, lotions, and hair care products.', '2', '4'),
	('Cetyl Alcohol', 'Cetyl Alcohol is a fatty alcohol used as an emollient, thickener, and stabilizer. It softens skin, improves texture, and enhances the consistency of creams and lotions.', '1', '3'),
	('Behenic Acid', 'It helps to moisturize and smooth the skin while improving the texture of creams and lotions.', '1', '4'),
