	('PEG-80 Sorbitan Laurate', 'It is an emulsifier, which means that it helps to mix together ingredients that would normally separate, such as oil and water. PEG-80 Sorbitan Laurate is typically a clear to pale yellow liquid. Being derived from natural sources, it is a safe and popular choice for a number of products. It also acts as a surfactant, helping to reduce surface tension and increase the spreadability of products.', '3', '3'),
	('Sodium Cocoyl Isethionate', 'Sodium Cocoyl Isethionate is a naturally-derived ingredient that comes from the fatty acids that are present in isethionic acid and coconut oil. These fatty acids are reacted with sodium isethionate and the mixture is heated to remove any water left behind. Further, the mixture is distilled to remove excess fatty acids. In its raw form, Sodium Cocoyl Isethionate appears as a fine white powder.', '1', '3'),
	('Lauryl Hydroxysultaine', 'It has a unique molecular structure that makes it effective in cleansing, foaming, and conditioning. Lauryl Hydroxysultaine appears as a clear to yellowish liquid with a faint odor that is soluble in water. This ingredient is known for its ability to create a rich lather while being gentle on the scalp and hair. When used in shampoos, Lauryl Hydroxysultaine helps to remove dirt, oil, and impurities without stripping the hair of its natural oils, leaving it clean and healthy-looking.', '1', '3'),
	('Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Oil', 'Persea Gratissima Butter effectivly moisturizes skin, improves elasticity, and protects from envairmental damaging factors.', '1', '2'),
	('Rosmarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Oil', 'A natural essential oil rich in antioxidants with antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stressors, promotes circulation, and has a refreshing, invigorating scent. Often used in skincare for its soothing and purifying effects.', '4', '3'),
	('Citrus Aurantium Bergamia (Bergamot) Fruit Oil', 'A natural essential oil extracted from bergamot fruit, known for its antibacterial, anti-inflammatory, and soothing properties. It helps regulate sebum production, reduce acne, and brighten the skin. Also provides a fresh, citrusy aroma.', '4', '3'),
	('Sodium Citrate', 'A sodium salt of citric acid used as a pH regulator and buffering agent in skincare formulations. It helps maintain the product''s stability, enhances preservative effectiveness, and provides mild antioxidant properties.', '1', '2'),
	('Acetyl Glucosamine', 'Acetyl Glucosamine is an amino sugar that comes from glucose and supports hydration, exfoliation, and anti-aging in cosmetic products. It attracts and retains moisture in the skin leaving it soft, smooth, and supple. It has exfoliating properties similar to alpha-hydroxy acids (AHAs), but with a lower potential for irritation. Additionally, this ingredient inhibits melanin production making it effective for reducing hyperpigmentation and evening out the skin tone. In its raw form, Acetyl Glucosamine appears as a white to off-white crystalline powder that is soluble in water - making it easier to incorporate into aqueous based formulations such as serums, creams, and gels. It is often paired with other active ingredients such as Niacinamide, Hyaluronic Acid, and Retinol for enhanced benefits.', '1', '3'),
	('Sodium Lactate', 'Sodium Lactate is a common ingredient used in cosmetics and personal care products. It is the sodium salt of lactic acid, a natural acid derived from the fermentation of sugars. Sodium Lactate is typically a clear, colorless liquid with a mild odor and serves multiple functions in skincare products. It acts as a humectant, attracting and retaining moisture in the skin, promoting hydration and preventing dryness. Additionally, Sodium Lactate can function as a pH regulator, helping to stabilize and adjust the pH of formulations.', '5', '2'),
	('Inonotus Obliquus (Mushroom) Extract', 'A powerful antioxidant-rich extract derived from Chaga mushrooms. It helps protect the skin from environmental stressors, supports skin regeneration, and provides anti-inflammatory benefits, making it suitable for soothing and revitalizing the skin.', null, null),
	('PCA', 'Pyrrolidone Carboxylic Acid (PCA) is a natural humectant that helps maintain skin hydration by attracting and retaining moisture. It is commonly found in the skin''s Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF) and plays a key role in keeping the skin soft, smooth, and healthy.', '2', '2'),
	('Dibutyl Adipate', 'Dibutyl Adipate is an ester with excellent emollient, film-forming, and solvent properties. It is widely used in cosmetic formulations to enhance product spreadability and provide a silky-smooth finish. It forms a lightweight and non-greasy film that softens and smooths the surface of the skin. Additionally, this ingredient enhances product stability and uniformity by dissolving the active ingredients. In its raw form, Dibutyl Adipate appears as a clear and colorless oily liquid with a mild, ester-like odor. It is commonly added to products like moisturizers, sunscreens, foundations, and leave-in products.', '1', '2'),
	('Polymethylsilsesquioxane', 'Polymethylsilsesquioxane is an ingredient widely used in the world of cosmetics. It comes in powder form and has round particles. The primary function of Polymethylsilsesquioxane is its film-forming capabilities and conditioning of the skin and hair. It is also responsible for protecting the surface that it is applied on while also improving the feel and texture of formulations. Additionally, Polymethylsilsesquioxane is good for all skin types.', '1', '2'),
	('Diethylamino Hydroxybenzoyl Hexyl Benzoate', 'Diethylamino Hydroxybenzoyl Hexyl Benzoate, also known as Uvinul A Plus, is a chemical compound commonly used in cosmetics and sunscreens for its excellent UV-absorbing properties. Its chemical formula is C24H31NO4. As an organic UV filter, it plays a crucial role in protecting the skin from the harmful effects of UV radiation, particularly UVA and UVB rays. While it is generally regarded as safe, concerns have been raised about potential contaminants, highlighting the importance of purity in cosmetic formulations.', '3', '2'),
	('Caprylyl Methicone', 'Caprylyl methicone is a clear, colorless, low viscosity, volatile silicone fluid that has excellent spreadability and leaves a light, silky and smooth feel on the skin.', '2', '2'),
	('Diethylhexyl Butamido Triazone', 'Diethylhexyl Butamido Triazone is a type of UV filter that provides skin protection against harmful rays of the sun. These harsh radiations can cause severe damage to the skin - such as premature aging, sunburn, and also cancer. This ingredient is added to sunscreen products and can provide high SPF at lower concentrations. Other names of Diethylhexyl Butamido Triazone include Iscotrizinol and Uvasorb HEB. This filter is oil soluble and particularly effective for water resistant and water repellent formulations. It is safe for use when used within recommended concentrations. Additionally, Diethylhexyl Butamido Triazone can be identified by its solid form and white to off white color.', '1', '2'),
	('Polyglyceryl-3 Methylglucose Distearate', 'Polyglyceryl-3 Methylglucose Distearate is a gentle, plant-derived emulsifier commonly used in facial skincare products. It helps blend water and oil-based ingredients, creating a smooth and stable formula. Known for its moisturizing and skin-conditioning properties, it enhances product texture while providing a soft, non-greasy feel, making it ideal for creams, lotions, and serums.', '1', '2'),
	('Hydroxyethyl Urea', 'Hydroxyethyl urea is a low-molecular-weight, highly water-soluble, hygroscopic solid that functions as a moisturizer and humectant in cosmetics and personal care products. It is a derivative of urea, singly substituted with 2-ethanol. It is usually available as an aqueous solution in water.', '1', '2'),
	('Poly C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate', 'Poly C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate is a polymer used in facial skincare products as a thickener, stabilizer, and film-forming agent. It helps improve product texture, ensuring a smooth and lightweight feel while enhancing the stability of emulsions. Commonly found in creams, lotions, and sunscreens, it contributes to a non-greasy and elegant application.', '2', '2'),
	('Sodium Acrylates Crosspolymer-2', 'Sodium Acrylates Crosspolymer-2 is a lightweight polymer used in facial skincare products as a thickener and stabilizer. It helps create a smooth, non-sticky texture while enhancing product spreadability and absorption. Commonly found in gels, creams, and serums, it also improves hydration by forming a flexible film that locks in moisture.', '1', '2'),
	('Polyacrylate Crosspolymer-6', 'Polyacrylate Crosspolymer-6 is a multifunctional polymer used in facial skincare products to enhance texture, stability, and spreadability. It acts as a thickener and stabilizer, creating a smooth, lightweight, and non-greasy feel. Commonly found in gels, creams, and sunscreens, it helps improve product absorption and overall sensory experience.', '1', null),
	('Hydroxyacetophenone', 'Hydroxyacetophenone is a multifunctional ingredient in facial skincare products, primarily used as an antioxidant and preservative booster. It helps protect the skin from oxidative stress while enhancing the effectiveness of other preservatives, ensuring product stability. Known for its soothing properties, it also helps calm the skin, making it ideal for sensitive and irritation-prone skin formulations.', '1', '3'),
	('Cynanchum Atratum Extract', 'Cynanchum Atratum Extract is a botanical ingredient known for its soothing and anti-inflammatory properties in facial skincare products. Rich in bioactive compounds, it helps calm irritation, reduce redness, and support skin barrier function. Commonly used in creams, serums, and masks, it is ideal for sensitive or stressed skin, promoting a balanced and healthy complexion.', '1', '2'),
	('Lycium Chinense Fruit Extract', 'Lycium Chinense Fruit Extract, rich in antioxidants and vitamins, protects, hydrates, and promotes a youthful glow. It helps improve skin elasticity and is commonly used in serums, creams, and masks.', '1', '2'),
	('Althaea Rosea Flower Extract', 'Althaea Rosea Flower Extract is a soothing and hydrating ingredient in skincare, known for its anti-inflammatory properties. It helps calm irritation, moisturize, and improve skin softness, making it ideal for sensitive or dry skin in creams, serums, and masks', '1', '2'),
	('Rosmarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Extract', 'Rosmarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Extract is a natural antioxidant with anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stress, reduces redness, and supports a clear, healthy complexion. Commonly found in creams, serums, and toners.', '2', '3'),
	('Vaccinium Macrocarpon (Cranberry) Fruit Extract', 'Vaccinium Macrocarpon (Cranberry) Fruit Extract is a powerful antioxidant rich in vitamins and polyphenols. It helps protect the skin from environmental damage, boosts hydration, and promotes a bright, youthful complexion. Commonly used in serums, creams, and masks.', '1', '3'),
	('Methylpropanediol', 'Methyl propanediol is a glycol and belongs to a class of compounds called alkane diols, which may replace other glycols like propylene or butylene glycol. It is used in cosmetics and personal care products as a solvent and has good antimicrobial properties. It is a clear and colorless liquid.', '1', '2'),
	('Alcohol Denatured', 'Alcohol Denat (Denatured Alcohol) is a form of alcohol used in skincare products primarily as a solvent and preservative. It helps dissolve active ingredients and improve product absorption, while also preventing microbial growth. However, it can be drying and may irritate sensitive skin, so it''s often used in small amounts in toners, astringents, and sanitizing products.', '1', '4'),
	('Polyglyceryl-10 Laurate', 'Polyglyceryl-10 Laurate is a common ingredient used in the personal care and cosmetic industry as an emulsifier and surfactant. It is an ester of lauric acid and polyglycerin-10, which is derived from the polymerization of glycerin. Polyglyceryl-10 Laurate helps to stabilize oil and water mixtures, allowing for the creation of stable emulsions. This ingredient also enhances the spreadability and texture of products, improving their overall sensory attributes. Polyglyceryl-10 Laurate is often found in various skincare products, such as cleansers, creams, lotions, and makeup removers.', '1', '2'),
	('Capryloyl Salicylic Acid', 'Capryloyl Salicylic Acid is a gentle exfoliant and acne-fighting ingredient in skincare. It helps to clear clogged pores, reduce inflammation, and promote smoother skin by removing dead skin cells. Known for its ability to provide exfoliation without irritation, it is commonly used in products for acne-prone or sensitive skin.', '5', '2'),
	('Houttuynia Cordata Extract', 'Houttuynia Cordata Extract is a plant-derived ingredient known for its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and soothing properties. It helps calm irritated skin, reduce redness, and protect the skin from environmental stressors. Often used in skincare for sensitive or acne-prone skin, it promotes a healthier and more balanced complexion.', '1', '2'),
	('Centella Asiatica Extract', 'Centella Asiatica Extract is a hydrocotyl extract of the Apiaceae plant Centella Asiatica L. The extract due to its active compounds like pentacyclic triterpenoids has many beneficial effects like anti-photoaging, healing of wounds and burns, cleansing, skin conditioning, etc.', '1', '4'),
	('Melaleuca Alternifolia (Tea Tree) Leaf Extract', 'Melaleuca Alternifolia (Tea Tree) Leaf Extract is known for its powerful antibacterial, antifungal, and anti-inflammatory properties. It helps to treat acne, reduce redness, and soothe irritated skin. Commonly used in skincare products for acne-prone or blemish-prone skin, it promotes clearer, healthier-looking skin.', '1', '3'),
	('Homosalate', 'Homosalate is a chemical compound commonly used in cosmetics and sunscreens as an ultraviolet (UV) filter, offering protection against sun-induced skin damage. Apart from this, it enhances the overall stability of sunscreen formulations. It is versatile and popular for its light, non-greasy texture, making it a preferred choice in various skincare products. While effective in UVB protection, it is important to note that Homosalate primarily addresses shorter-wavelength UV rays, necessitating the combination with other sunscreen agents for broad-spectrum coverage against both UVA and UVB rays.', '4', '4'),
	('Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer', 'Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer is a widely used ingredient in cosmetics and personal care. This compound helps form a film on the surface that it is applied to that feels good to the touch. It also controls the production of oil as it is a porous ingredient that has the capacity to absorb excess oil from the surface and prevent acne. In its raw form, Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer appears as a fine white powder or very tiny and highly porous spherical beads. It is slightly soluble in water.', '2', '2'),
	('Isoamyl P Methoxy Cinnamate', 'Isoamyl p-Methoxycinnamate is a UV filter used in sunscreens and skincare products to protect the skin from UVB radiation. It helps prevent sunburn and premature aging while being lightweight and non-greasy. Commonly found in sun protection formulations, it enhances skin defense against harmful sun exposure.', '1', '2'),
	('Methoxy PEG/PPG-25/4 Dimethicone', 'Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer is a widely used ingredient in cosmetics and personal care. This compound helps form a film on the surface that it is applied to that feels good to the touch. It also controls the production of oil as it is a porous ingredient that has the capacity to absorb excess oil from the surface and prevent acne. In its raw form, Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer appears as a fine white powder or very tiny and highly porous spherical beads. It is slightly soluble in water.', null, null),
	('PEG/PPG-20/5 Dimethicone', 'PEG/PPG-20/5 Dimethicone is a silicone-based emulsifier and skin-conditioning agent. It helps improve product texture, providing a smooth, lightweight feel while enhancing moisture retention. Commonly used in creams, lotions, and sunscreens, it creates a non-greasy, silky finish and enhances spreadability.', null, null),
	('Lotus Corniculatus (Bird''s Foot Trefoil) Flower Extract', 'Lotus Corniculatus (Bird''s Foot Trefoil) Flower Extract is a botanical ingredient known for its antioxidant and soothing properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stress, reduces redness, and promotes a calm, balanced complexion. Commonly used in skincare products for its gentle, skin-conditioning benefits.', '1', '2'),
	('Safflower Oil/Palm Oil Aminopropanediol Esters', 'Safflower Oil is a lightweight, non-comedogenic oil rich in linoleic acid and antioxidants. It helps moisturize, soothe, and protect the skin while supporting a healthy skin barrier. Commonly used in facial oils, creams, and serums, it promotes soft, smooth, and hydrated skin.', '1', null),
	('Vitamin B5', 'Vitamin B5, also known as Panthenol, is a powerful humectant and skin-conditioning agent. It helps hydrate, soothe, and repair the skin barrier while reducing redness and irritation. Commonly used in moisturizers, serums, and healing creams, it promotes soft, healthy, and resilient skin.', null, null),
	('Olive Oil', 'Olive Oil is a nutrient-rich emollient packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and fatty acids. It deeply moisturizes, nourishes, and protects the skin while supporting a healthy barrier. Commonly used in creams, serums, and cleansers, it promotes soft, smooth, and radiant skin.', null, null),
	('Peptides', 'Peptides are short chains of amino acids that help support collagen production, improve skin elasticity, and reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles. They enhance skin repair, hydration, and firmness, making them a key ingredient in anti-aging creams, serums, and eye treatments.', null, null),
	('Hydrolyzed Collagen', 'Collagen that has been converted into short chains of amino acids around 3–6 kilodaltons, is called hydrolyzed collagen and is also known as collagen peptides. Hydrolyzed Collagen is primarily used in skincare and hair preparations in cosmetics and personal care products, but it is also present in makeup, shampoos, and bath products. Unlike popular belief, hydrolyzed collagen is a humectant, which helps hydrate skin, rather than an anti-aging ingredient.', '1', '2'),
	('Aloe Yohju Matsu Ekisu', 'Aloe Yohju Matsu Ekisu is a plant-derived extract known for its soothing, hydrating, and anti-inflammatory properties. It helps calm irritated skin, retain moisture, and promote a healthy complexion. Commonly used in skincare products for sensitive or dry skin, it enhances skin hydration and comfort.', '1', null),
	('Glycereth-26', 'Glycereth-26 is a polyethylene glycol ether of glycerin. It serves as an emollient and humectant, known for its ability to attract and retain moisture in the skin, providing hydration and improving skin smoothness.', '2', '2'),
	('Arbutin', 'A natural derivative of hydroquinone found in plants like bearberry. It gradually converts into hydroquinone in the skin, providing a gentle brightening effect.', '1', '3'),
	('Adenosine', 'Adenosine is a skin-soothing and anti-aging ingredient known for its ability to reduce wrinkles, improve skin elasticity, and promote a smoother complexion. It helps boost collagen production and has anti-inflammatory properties, making it ideal for anti-aging creams, serums, and moisturizers.', '1', '2'),
	('Dicaprylyl Carbonate', 'Dicaprylyl carbonate is a colorless and almost odorless component that conditions the skin and hair - leaving them smoother and softer. Even though it is essentially an oil, it does not make the surface greasy or oily. Additionally, it also increases the spreadability of the formulations', '1', '2'),
	('Cetearyl Alcohol/ Dicetyl Phosphate/ Ceteth-10 Phosphate', 'Cetearyl Alcohol, Dicetyl Phosphate, and Ceteth-10 Phosphate are emulsifiers that stabilize, thicken, and improve the texture of skincare products, ensuring smooth and non-greasy application.', null, null),
	('Medicago Sativa (Alfalfa) Extract', 'Medicago Sativa (alfalfa) Extract. Also called lucerne, Alfalfa Extract by Carrubba is highly nutritive. It has a high degree of chlorophyll for cleansing and purifying hair and body, inside and out. It is high in vitamin K, A, D, protein and minerals. It helps conditioning and strengthening the hair. Also has a stimulating effect of the growth of supportive connective tissue cells. Provides antifungal and antiinflammatory properties. Alfalfa Extract is used in shampoo, conditioner, skin care and styling products.', '1', '2'),
	('Ethylene/ Acrylic Acid Copolymer', 'Ethylene/Acrylic Acid Copolymer is a polymer used in skincare products to improve texture and stability. It acts as a thickener and film-forming agent, helping to enhance product consistency and provide a smooth, spreadable finish.', '3', '2'),
	('Papain/ Carbomer/ 1,2-Hexanediol/ Caprylyl Glycol/ Algin', 'Papain, an enzyme derived from papayas, digests keratin proteins to help accelerate exfoliation leaving the skin softer and smoother. It provides antioxidant and anti-inflammatory benefits as well.', null, null),
	('Hydrolyzed Opuntia Ficus-Indica Flower Extract', 'Hydrolyzed Opuntia Ficus-Indica Flower Extract in cosmetics is derived from the flowers of the prickly pear cactus through a hydrolysis process. This extract is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and amino acids. Renowned for its hydrating and skin-soothing properties, Hydrolyzed Opuntia Ficus-Indica Flower Extract aids in moisturizing and revitalizing the skin. The hydrolysis enhances the extract''s absorption, allowing for better penetration into the skin. Its inclusion in skincare formulations, such as serums and moisturizers, helps promote skin suppleness, protect against environmental stressors, and contributes to a more radiant and nourished complexion with the benefits of prickly pear''s natural goodness.', '1', null),
	('Alpha-Arbutin', 'A more stable and potent synthetic form of Arbutin. It has better water solubility and is more effective at inhibiting melanin production, making it work faster and more efficiently for skin brightening.', '1', '3'),
	('Isononyl Isononanoate', 'Isononyl isononanoate is an emollient ester with a rich and creamy but non-greasy feel. It softens the skin. The esters of nonanoic acid occur naturally in the oil of pelargonium, a group of flowering plants. It has unique characteristics including extremely low freeze point, low viscosity, and excellent solubility and compatibility in a variety of ingredients such as esters, volatile silicones, mineral, and vegetable oils. Isononyl isononanoate in skin care helps to maintain the skin’s softness and plasticity while forming a semi-occlusive film that moisturizes the skin, reduces the itchy sensation of dry skin, and improves the stratum corneum, which is the outermost layer of the skin by preventing the evaporation of the skin’s natural moisture. It also functions as an antistatic agent which reduces static electricity and prevents the hair or skin to be electrically charged.', '1', '2'),
	('Octadecenedioic Acid', 'Octadecenedioic Acid is a fatty acid used in skincare for its moisturizing and soothing properties. It helps improve skin texture, reduce irritation, and support the skin''s natural barrier, often found in products aimed at hydration and calming sensitive skin.', '1', null),
	('1-Methylhydantoin-2-Imide', '1-Methylhydantoin-2-Imide, also called Creatinine, Creatinine dissolves in water and other polar solvents very quickly and can be added coldly into formulations. 1-Methylhydantoin-2-Imide is a conditioner that can be used for manufacturing special cosmetics that lighten the skin. Besides its lightening effect on color pigments, Creatinine also gives skin a brighter and more uniform appearance, making it ideal for use in skin conditioners. It is also helpful in age spot-fading creams. Its recommended concentration is between 0.5 and 1.0 percent.', '1', '3'),
	('Butylene Glycol/ Scutellaria Baicalensis Root Extract', 'Butylene glycol is one of the most popular ingredients used in cosmetic and skin care products. It is colorless and viscous with the chemical formula C4H10O2. It comes in a liquid form and acts as a humectant, emollient, and solvent in formulations. Butylene glycol is the perfect ingredient for moisturizing, protecting, and conditioning the skin and hair. It also acts as a solvent and keeps the products from clamping up.', '1', '3'),
	('Acetyl Tyrosine', 'Acetyl Tyrosine is a modified form of the amino acid tyrosine, known for its antioxidant and skin-soothing properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stressors, supports the skin''s natural repair processes, and enhances skin hydration.', '1', '2'),
	('Bisabolol', 'Bisabolol, more formally αlpha-bisabolol or also known as levomenol, is a natural monocyclic sesquiterpene alcohol. It is a colorless to light yellow, oily liquid, that is the primary constituent of the essential oil from German chamomile (Matricaria recutita) and Myoporum crassifolium. It is used in cosmetic formulations as a skin conditioning agent. It has a weak sweet floral aroma and is used in various fragrances.', '2', '2'),
	('Cyclotetrapeptide-24 Aminocyclohexane Carboxylate', 'Mimics cellular communication, focusing on accelerating cellular repair and anti-aging.', '1', '2'),
	('Saccharomyces Cerevisiae Extract', 'Saccharomyces Cerevisiae Extract is a yeast-derived ingredient rich in antioxidants, amino acids, and vitamins. It helps brighten the skin, improve hydration, and support the skin’s natural renewal process. Commonly found in anti-aging and hydrating skincare products, it promotes a radiant and healthy complexion.', '1', '3'),
	('Methylsilanol Mannuronate', 'Methylsilanol Mannuronate is a skin-conditioning and anti-aging ingredient derived from brown algae. It helps improve skin elasticity, hydrate, and protect against free radicals. Commonly found in firming and moisturizing skincare products, it supports skin structure and reduces the appearance of fine lines.', '1', null),
	('Palmitoyl Hexapeptide-12', 'Palmitic acid attached to peptide to yield more lipophilic structure considerably enhances the skin penetration levels, efficiency, and power. It enables potentiation or even initiation of the cosmetic activity that requires the transport of the peptide to the living tissues of the skin.', '1', null),
	('Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil', 'Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil is a common cosmetic ingredient which is a white or pale yellow waxy substance that is solid at room temperature, but melts when applied to the skin. In the cosmetic industry, hydrogenated vegetable oil is commonly used as an emollient, which helps to soften and smooth the skin. It is also used as a thickening agent to create the desired texture of cosmetic products such as lotions, creams, and lip balms. Hydrogenated vegetable oil is valued for its stability, as it has a long shelf life and does not easily spoil or become rancid. Its versatility and compatibility with other cosmetic ingredients make it a popular choice for many cosmetic formulations.', '1', '2'),
	('Polygonum Fagopyrum Seed Extract', 'Polygonum Fagopyrum (Buckwheat) Seed Extract is rich in antioxidants, polyphenols, and flavonoids, helping to protect the skin from environmental damage. It has soothing and anti-inflammatory properties, making it beneficial for reducing redness and improving skin hydration. Commonly used in anti-aging and calming skincare products.', '1', '2'),
	('Diethylhexyl Adipate', 'Diethylhexyl Adipate, also known as Dioctyl Adipate, is a plasticizer used in cosmetics to make formulations softer and less brittle. It improves the durability of the products and prevents cracking or chipping. With its mild aromatic scent, this ingredient enhances the sensory experience of beauty products. Diethylhexyl Adipate is also used as a skin conditioning agent and emollient. It can trap moisture on the skin and give it a soft and smooth appearance. In its raw state, it is a clear, colorless to pale yellow viscous liquid. This film forming agent can also be used to dissolve other ingredients in a formulation.', '4', '3'),
	('Citrullus Vulgaris (Watermelon) Fruit Extract', 'Citrullus Vulgaris (Watermelon) Fruit Extract is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and amino acids. It helps hydrate, soothe, and protect the skin from environmental stressors while promoting a fresh and radiant complexion. Commonly used in moisturizing and anti-aging skincare products.', '1', '2'),
	('Pyrus Malus (Apple) Fruit Extract', 'Pyrus Malus (Apple) Fruit Extract is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and natural acids that help exfoliate, hydrate, and brighten the skin. It promotes a smoother complexion, improves moisture retention, and protects against environmental damage. Commonly used in anti-aging, hydrating, and brightening skincare products.', '1', '3'),
	('Lens Esculenta (Lentil) Fruit Extract', 'Lens Esculenta (Lentil) Fruit Extract is a natural skin-conditioning ingredient rich in antioxidants, proteins, and vitamins. It helps hydrate the skin, refine pores, and improve overall texture. Commonly used in moisturizing and pore-minimizing skincare products.', '1', '3'),
	('Ascorbyl Tetraisopalmitate', 'Ascorbyl Tetraisopalmitate is a stable and oil-soluble derivative of Vitamin C commonly used in cosmetics and skincare products. Also known as Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, it offers potent antioxidant properties, protecting the skin from free radicals and environmental damage such as UV radiation and pollution. Ascorbyl Tetraisopalmitate is highly bioavailable, penetrating deep into the skin to stimulate collagen production, reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, and promote skin firmness and elasticity.', '1', '2'),
	('Secale Cereale (Rye) Seed Extract', 'Secale Cereale (Rye) Seed Extract is known for its firming and anti-aging properties. It helps improve skin elasticity, smooth fine lines, and enhance hydration. Commonly used in lifting and rejuvenating skincare products.', '1', '3'),
	('Cellulose Acetate Butyrate', 'Cellulose Acetate Butyrate is a film-forming and texture-enhancing ingredient in skincare. It helps improve product spreadability, provides a smooth finish, and enhances moisture retention. Commonly found in creams and serums for better application and skin feel.', '1', '2'),
	('Ursolic Acid', 'Ursolic Acid is a naturally occurring pentacyclic triterpenoid found in various plants, including apples, rosemary, basil, and certain berries. It is widely used in cosmetics and personal care products due to its anti-aging and skin repairing benefits. It strengthens the skin barrier and maintains hydration while also promoting collagen production to improve elasticity. In its raw form, Ursolic Acid appears as a white to off-white crystalline powder with a fine texture and slightly herbal odor.', '2', '2'),
	('Chitosan', 'Chitosan is a remarkable ingredient found in cosmetics, renowned for its natural and multifunctional properties. Derived from chitin, a substance found in the exoskeletons of crustaceans like shrimp and crabs, chitosan is harnessed for its skincare benefits. With its high biocompatibility, chitosan becomes a favorable choice for cosmetics. It forms a protective film on the skin, locking in moisture and shielding it from environmental aggressors. Moreover, chitosan boasts excellent adhesion and film-forming properties, making it an ideal component in cosmetics like creams and lotions.', '1', '3'),
	('Methylparaben', 'Methylparaben is a synthetic preservative commonly used in cosmetics and personal care products. Its primary function is to extend the shelf life of these products by inhibiting the growth of harmful bacteria and molds. Methylparaben appears as a white, odorless, crystalline powder and is known for its efficacy and cost-effectiveness in preventing microbial contamination. Its chemical formula is C8H8O3. While it has been widely used in the past, concerns have arisen regarding its safety, leading to increased scrutiny and the exploration of alternative preservatives in the cosmetic industry to address potential health and environmental issues.', '4', '2'),
	('Glycosyl Trehalose', 'Glycosyl Trehalose is a sugar-based humectant and antioxidant that helps retain moisture and protect the skin from oxidative stress. It improves hydration, enhances skin barrier function, and provides anti-aging benefits. Commonly used in moisturizing and soothing skincare products.', '1', null),
	('PEG-240/ HDI Copolymer Bis-Decyltetradeceth-20 Ether', 'PEG-240/ HDI Copolymer Bis-Decyltetradeceth-20 Ether is a film-forming and stabilizing agent used in skincare products. It helps improve texture, enhance spreadability, and create a smooth, lightweight finish on the skin. Commonly found in serums, gels, and hydrating formulations.', '2', '2'),
	('Hydrogenated Starch Hydrolysate', 'Hydrogenated Starch Hydrolysate is a humectant and skin-conditioning agent derived from starch. It helps retain moisture, smooth the skin, and enhance hydration. Commonly used in moisturizing and anti-aging skincare products.', '1', '2'),
	('Betula Platyphylla Japonica Juice', 'Betula Platyphylla Japonica Juice (Japanese White Birch Juice) is a nutrient-rich botanical extract known for its hydrating, soothing, and antioxidant properties. It helps replenish moisture, calm irritation, and improve skin elasticity. Commonly used in moisturizing and soothing skincare products.', '1', null),
	('Gardenia Florida Fruit Extract', 'Gardenia Florida Fruit Extract is a natural antioxidant and skin-conditioning ingredient. It helps soothe the skin, provides anti-inflammatory benefits, and has potential brightening properties. Commonly used in skincare for its calming and protective effects.', null, null),
	('Sea Water', 'Sea Water is rich in minerals like magnesium, calcium, and potassium, which help hydrate, soothe, and strengthen the skin barrier. It also has antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties, making it beneficial for acne-prone and sensitive skin. Commonly used in hydrating and soothing skincare products.', '1', null),
	('Monascus Extract', 'Monascus Extract is derived from Monascus, a type of red yeast. It is known for its antioxidant and skin-brightening properties, helping to protect the skin from oxidative stress and promote an even complexion. Commonly used in brightening and anti-aging skincare products.', '1', '2'),
	('Potassium Laurate', 'Potassium Laurate is a potassium salt of lauric acid, commonly used as an emulsifier and surfactant in skincare products. It helps cleanse the skin by breaking down oils and dirt while also contributing to product stability and texture. Often found in cleansers and emulsified formulations.', '1', '2'),
	('Glyceryl Caprylate', 'Glyceryl Caprylate is a multifunctional ingredient commonly used in cosmetics as a preservative, moisturizer, and emollient. As a preservative, it helps extend the shelf life of cosmetic products by inhibiting the growth of microorganisms. Additionally, it contributes to the texture and feel of formulations, acting as an emollient to soften and smooth the skin. Its mildness makes it suitable for sensitive skin. Glyceryl Caprylate is often preferred by cosmetic manufacturers seeking alternatives to traditional synthetic preservatives due to its relatively natural origin and compatibility with various product types.', '1', '2'),
	('Carthamus Tinctorius (Safflower) Flower Extract', 'Carthamus Tinctorius Flower Extract is a traditional ingredient valued for its benefits. It functions as a high-grade cosmetic dyeing agent. Unfortunately, the beauty industry has replaced this ingredient with cheaper synthetic dyes. This natural flower extract supports skin whitening, anti-aging, and deep hydration. Also known as Safflower Flower Extract, Carthamus Tinctorius Flower Extract protects both the skin and products from UVA and UVB radiation. It contains flavonoids and phenolic compounds that neutralize free radicals. These help reduce fine lines and wrinkles. It is safe and well-tolerated by most skin types.', '1', '2'),
	('Laminaria Japonica Extract', 'Laminaria Japonica Extract is a popular ingredient in cosmetics due to its hydrating, detoxifying, and anti-aging benefits. It has a rich nutrient profile, namely vitamins, minerals, amino acids, phenolic compounds, and polysaccharides - essential for overall skin and hair health. Also known as Japanese Kelp or Kombu, this ingredient has been used for centuries to draw out impurities from the skin and support its barrier function. In its raw form, Laminaria Japonica Extract appears as a light to medium brown liquid with a slightly viscous consistency. It is commonly added to products like moisturizers, serums, cleansers, sunscreens, and shampoos. This extract is derived from natural sources and is largely safe for use.', '3', '2'),
	('Undaria Pinnatifida Extract', 'Undaria Pinnatifida Extract (Wakame Seaweed Extract) is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. It helps hydrate, protect against environmental stressors, and improve skin elasticity. Commonly used in anti-aging and moisturizing skincare products.', '3', '2'),
	('Fucus Vesiculosus Extract', 'Fucus Vesiculosus Extract is a natural and highly effective antioxidant that is used in various cosmetics and personal care products. It protects the skin and hair against pollution and free radicals that damage the skin leading to dullness and premature aging. This ingredient is also anti-inflammatory, soothing, and texture enhancing. Fucus Vesiculosus Extract is the INCI name of Bladderwrack Extract and appears as a yellowish-brown liquid. It is packed with high concentrations of minerals and amino acids that greatly benefit the skin. It can be found in formulations like shampoos, conditions, and face cleansers.', '4', '3'),
	('Maltodextrin', 'Maltodextrin in cosmetics is a carbohydrate-based ingredient derived from starch, often sourced from corn, rice, or potatoes. It serves as a versatile additive with multiple functions. In powdered cosmetics, it acts as a bulking agent, improving texture and dispersion. In skincare, it can enhance product feel, stability, and absorption. Maltodextrin''s water-absorbing properties also make it valuable in dry shampoos and oil-controlling formulations. Further, this ingredient appears as a white, odorless powder.', '1', '2'),
	('Hydrogenated Lecithin', 'Hydrogenated Lecithin is a yellowish-brown ingredient that is commonly used in cosmetics and personal care products due to its high hydrating properties. It can immensely reduce symptoms of dryness and irritation by deeply moisturizing the surface. Hydrogenated Lecithin also mixes well with oil and water-based ingredients, thus acting as a good emulsifier in the products. This versatile ingredient improves the feel of both the product and the surface on which it is applied.', '2', '2'),
	('Octyldodeceth-16', 'Octyldodeceth-16 is a nonionic emulsifier and surfactant used in skincare products. It helps improve the texture and stability of formulations by allowing oil and water to mix effectively. It also enhances the spreadability and absorption of active ingredients. Commonly found in creams, lotions, and serums.', '2', '3'),
	('C12-14 Sec-pareth-12', 'C12-14 Sec-Pareth-12 is a surfactant and emulsifier commonly used in skincare products. It helps improve the texture, stability, and spreadability of formulations. It also aids in cleansing by helping to remove oils and impurities from the skin, making it a common ingredient in cleansers and body washes.', null, null),
	('PEG-100 Stearate', 'PEG-100 Stearate is an ingredient that is used in a variety of cosmetic and skin care products to control the texture and flow of the formulations. In its raw form, it looks like a pasty or waxy solid that is cream in color and has a faint odor. PEG-100 Stearate is also an excellent emollient that leaves the skin and hair moisturized. It is mainly added to products like cleansers, moisturizers, mascaras, and shampoos.', '2', '3'),
	('Cetearyl Olivate', 'Cetearyl Olivate is an emulsifying agent derived from olive oil. It helps to stabilize and blend oil and water in formulations, enhancing the texture of skincare products. It also has moisturizing and skin-conditioning properties, making it suitable for hydrating and soothing dry or sensitive skin. Commonly found in creams, lotions, and moisturizers.', '1', '2'),
	('Sorbitan Olivate', 'Sorbitan Olivate is a versatile and effective ingredient used in a wide variety of cosmetic and personal care products. Derived from olive oil and sorbitol, it is also a natural ingredient. It appears as a waxy, light yellow to beige substance that is soluble in both oil and water. This ingredient is used as an emulsifier, meaning it helps to combine oil and water-based ingredients in a formulation. It creates a smooth, creamy texture and helps in stabilizing the formulation.', '1', null),
	('Sodium Lauroyl Lactylate', 'Sodium Lauroyl Lactylate is an anionic surfactant and emulsifier that is derived naturally and used extensively in personal care and cosmetics. It appears as a white to off-white power in its raw form and is highly soluble in oils. It stabilizes oil-in-water emulsions, ensuring a uniform and consistent texture in creams, lotions, and serums. Additionally, Sodium Lauroyl Lactylate gently cleanses by removing dirt and oil without stripping the skin’s natural moisture, making it ideal for sensitive or dry skin formulations. It is commonly found in face washes, shampoos, creams, and conditioners.', '1', null),
	('Decyl Oleate', 'Decyl Oleate is a cosmetic ingredient valued for its emollient properties and is often used as an alternative to Mulsifan. It serves as a skin-conditioning agent and lipid layer enhancer, promoting a smooth and soft feel in various formulations. The formula of Decyl Oleate, C20H40O2, denotes a compound composed of a decyl alcohol chain and an oleic acid chain. Decyl Oleate acts as a lightweight moisturizer, aiding in the spreadability of products. This versatile ester finds application in skincare, haircare, and makeup, contributing to a luxurious texture while improving the overall sensory experience of cosmetic formulations.', '1', '2'),
	('Benzophenone-3', 'Benzophenone-3, often labeled as oxybenzone in sunscreen products, is a widely used chemical compound in cosmetics and sunscreens. Its chemical formula is C14H12O3. This organic UV filter serves as a sunblock agent, absorbing and dissipating harmful ultraviolet (UV) rays, particularly UVB and some UVA radiation. Benzophenone-3 helps protect the skin from sunburn and UV-induced damage, making it a common ingredient in sunscreens, lotions, and lip balms. Despite its effectiveness in shielding against sun damage, concerns about its potential hormone-disrupting properties have led to ongoing research and the exploration of alternative UV filters in the cosmetic industry.', null, null),
	('Isopropyl Palmitate', 'Isopropyl Palmitate is a clear and colorless ingredient with a pleasant odor. In cosmetics and personal care, it is used primarily as an emollient that helps to soothe and soften the skin. For this reason, Isopropyl Palmitate is quite popular in products like moisturizers, lotions, and creams. Additionally, it is not a paraben and does not contain any preservatives that may be harmful to the skin. This ingredient is also beneficial in enhancing the texture of the products that it is added to.', '1', '3'),
	('Macadamia Integrifolia (Macadamia) Nut Oil', 'Macadamia Integrifolia Seed Oil is a conditioning agent loaded with nourishing fatty acids. It is popular because of the presence of a rare fatty acid - palmitoleic acid - that deeply hydrates the skin and leaves it soft and supple. It can also be used for healing scars, minor wounds, and sunburn. Macadamia Integrifolia Seed Oil is also commonly known as Macadamia Oil and has a golden yellow color. It rapidly absorbs into the skin making it quite effective. This plant oil works best on dry and sensitive skin and is quite similar to human sebum. Lastly, Macadamia Integrifolia Seed Oil is a natural ingredient and safe for use.', '1', '2'),
	('Glycine Soja (Soybean) Oil', 'Glycine Soja Oil is a great emollient and moisturizer that can be used on both skin and hair. It nourishes and hydrates the surface, leaving it soft, smooth, and supple. Glycine Soja Oil is also known as soybean oil and has high contents of replenishing fatty acids, particularly linoleic and oleic acid. This lightweight oil has excellent spreadability, which makes it a popular choice for cosmetics. Further, rich in antioxidants such as vitamin E, Glycine Soja Oil also offers protective benefits against environmental stressors, helping to maintain skin health and vitality in various personal care formulations.', '1', '3'),
	('Triticum Vulgare (Wheat) Bran Extract', 'Triticum Vulgare (Wheat) Bran Extract is rich in vitamins, antioxidants, and minerals, making it beneficial for skin health. It has anti-inflammatory and moisturizing properties and helps improve skin texture. This extract is often used in skincare for its ability to soothe, hydrate, and promote a healthy-looking complexion.', '1', '3'),
	('Hydrolyzed Milk Protein', 'Hydrolyzed milk protein or hydrolysed milk protein is a milk hydrolyzate. It is a hydrolyzed phosphoprotein with a mild flavor, that is created by extracting the best possible dairy protein from natural sources. This milk-derived protein is a fantastic moisturizer that gives the skin and hair the ideal ratio of nutrients.', '1', '2'),
	('Sorbitan Stearate', 'Sorbitan Stearate is a common ingredient in cosmetics and skincare products, serving as an emulsifier and stabilizer. It is derived from the natural sugar alcohol, sorbitan, and stearic acid, a fatty acid. This combination forms a waxy, cream-colored substance with a characteristic mild odor. As an emulsifier, Sorbitan Stearate helps blend water and oil-based ingredients, enabling the formulation of smooth and homogeneous products like creams and lotions. Its stabilizing properties prevent the separation of different components, ensuring a consistent texture and appearance. With its versatility and stability, Sorbitan Stearate plays a crucial role in creating effective and visually appealing cosmetic formulations.', '1', '3'),
	('Cetyl Dimethicone', 'Cetyl Dimethicone is a silicone-based ingredient commonly used in cosmetics. It is a clear, viscous liquid with excellent skin-conditioning properties. Cetyl Dimethicone helps to enhance the texture and spreadability of cosmetic products, giving them a silky and smooth feel upon application. It forms a protective barrier on the skin, helping to prevent moisture loss and providing a soft, velvety finish. Cetyl Dimethicone is also gluten-free, making it suitable for individuals with gluten sensitivities. Additionally, this ingredient is not water-soluble and requires the use of emulsifiers or other solubilizers for incorporation into water-based formulations.', '2', '2'),
	('CI 19140', 'CI 19140 or Tartrazine is a very common colorant used in variety of cosmetic products. It is used globally for imparting the color yellow (lemon shade). It has been approved by the U.S. Food and Drugs Administration (FDA) for use in cosmetics but is regulated.', '5', '4'),
	('CI 14720', 'CI 14720 or Carmoisine is a coloring agent that is widely used in the cosmetic industry. It imparts a red color to formulations and is also quite long lasting. It can also be maroonish to reddish brown depending on the manufacturing process. CI 14720 can be commonly found in products such as lipsticks, eye shadows, face powders, blusher and also sometimes in shampoos and hair dyes. Carmoisine comes in the form of a powder that is also soluble in water.', '5', '3'),
	('CI 42090', 'CI 42090 is a synthetic compound that gives a brilliant blue color to products like shampoos, hair colors, and soaps. It is basically a colorant that is widely prevalent in the cosmetic industry. It is also known by other names such as Blue 1 CI 42090 or CI 42090 Blue 1. It comes in powder form and is highly concentrated when used as a primary color. That said, it can also be mixed with other colorants to produce a wide range of hues and shades.', '8', '3'),
	('C12-14 Pareth-12', 'C12-14 Pareth-12 is a surfactant and emulsifying agent derived from fatty alcohols. It is used in skincare products to help cleanse the skin by breaking down oils and impurities. It also helps improve the texture and stability of formulations by enabling oil and water to mix effectively, making it a common ingredient in cleansers, shampoos, and body washes.', '1', '2'),
	('Citrus Grandis (Grapefruit) Peel Oil', 'Citrus Grandis (Grapefruit) Peel Oil is known for its refreshing scent and antioxidant properties. It helps balance oily skin, promotes a clear complexion, and has astringent and antibacterial effects.', '6', '4'),
	('Laminaria Saccharina Extract', 'Laminaria Saccharina Extract is derived from a type of brown seaweed. It has hydrating, soothing, and antioxidant properties, helping to improve skin moisture retention and protect against environmental stressors. It is commonly used in skincare for its anti-aging and revitalizing effects.', '3', '2'),
	('Polyglyceryl-3 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone', 'Polyglyceryl-3 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone is a silicone-based emulsifier that helps blend oil and water-based ingredients in skincare and cosmetics. It enhances product spreadability, provides a smooth texture, and improves skin feel without a greasy residue. Commonly found in sunscreens, moisturizers, and foundations.', '2', null),
	('Triethoxysilylethyl Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Hexyl Dimethicone', 'Triethoxysilylethyl Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Hexyl Dimethicone is a silicone-based film-forming agent that enhances water resistance and long-lasting wear in skincare and cosmetic products. It helps improve product adherence, provides a smooth, silky texture, and contributes to a lightweight, non-greasy feel, commonly found in sunscreens and foundations.', '2', null),
	('Phenoxyethyl Caprylate', 'Phenoxyethyl Caprylate is an emollient and skin-conditioning agent that enhances the texture and spreadability of skincare products. It provides a lightweight, non-greasy feel while helping to improve moisture retention and product absorption. Often used in sunscreens and moisturizers for a smooth, silky finish.', null, null),
	('Zinc PCA', 'Zinc PCA is basically derived from Zinc and is used for conditioning the skin. It is becoming one of the most loved ingredients in the world of skin care because of its numerous benefits. Apart from deeply moisturizing and hydrating the skin, it also fights acne-causing germs and leaves the skin supple and smooth. Moreover, it also fights the signs of aging. The full form of Zinc PCA is Zinc Pyrrolidone Carboxylic Acid. It is a compound that is natural and is known for aiding the tightening of the skin.', '4', '3'),
	('Polyglyceryl-10 Diisostearate', 'Polyglyceryl-10 Diisostearate is an emulsifier and skin-conditioning agent that helps blend oil and water-based ingredients in skincare products. It provides a lightweight, non-greasy feel and enhances the spreadability of formulations, often found in cleansers, creams, and sunscreens.', '1', '2'),
	('Dictyopteris Membrancea Extract', 'Dictyopteris Membranacea Extract is a marine-derived ingredient known for its skin-brightening and anti-aging properties. It helps improve skin radiance, even out skin tone, and provides hydration, making it a popular addition to skincare formulations targeting dull or uneven skin.', '3', null),
	('Lauryl PEG-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone', 'Lauryl PEG-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone is a silicone-based emulsifier and surfactant that helps blend oil and water in skincare formulations. It enhances product spreadability, provides a smooth texture, and offers a lightweight, non-greasy feel on the skin.', '2', null),
	('Undecane / Tridecane', 'Undecane / Tridecane are lightweight, biodegradable emollients that act as natural silicone alternatives. They provide a smooth, non-greasy texture, enhance spreadability, and improve skin feel in skincare formulations.', null, '2'),
	('Plankton Extract', 'Plankton Extract is a nutrient-rich ingredient known for its antioxidant, hydrating, and skin-rejuvenating properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stressors while promoting a healthy, radiant complexion.', '1', '2'),
	('Dimethicone Crosspolymer', 'Dimethicone Crosspolymer is a silicone-based polymer used as a thickening agent, emulsifier, and stabilizer in cosmetics. It improves the texture, spreadability, and slip of formulations, while also creating a protective barrier on the skin to prevent moisture loss. It is commonly found in sunscreens, primers, and moisturizers due to its ability to enhance the product''s performance and provide a smooth sensory experience. The appearance of Dimethicone Crosspolymer is a white powder', '2', null),
	('CI 77492, CI 77491, CI 77499', 'CI 77492 is a dye of mineral origin also called Iron Oxide. It gives products their yellow color. It is often mixed with other iron oxides like CI 77491 (red) and CI 77499 (black) to represent different hues. It is authorized in organic.', null, null),
	('Triethoxycaprylylsilane', 'Triethoxycaprylylsilane is a clear-to-yellow liquid that functions as a binder, skin conditioning agent, and surface modifier in cosmetics. It is used to coat pigments used in cosmetics and personal care products. Triethoxycaprylylsilane contains a Si-O bond that can be readily hydrolyzed in the presence of moisture, making this compound very reactive', '1', '3'),
	('Oleic Acid', 'Oleic Acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid widely used in cosmetics and skincare products. It is derived from various vegetable oils, such as olive oil and sunflower oil. Oleic Acid appears as a pale yellow to amber-colored liquid with a mild odor. In cosmetics, it serves as an emollient and moisturizing ingredient due to its ability to enhance skin hydration and improve skin barrier function. It is often found in creams, lotions, serums, and lip balms, providing a smooth and soft texture while helping to maintain the skin''s moisture balance.', '1', '2'),
	('CI 77891 / Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate', 'A white pigment commonly used in sunscreens and cosmetics for UV protection and coverage. A mild, skin-friendly emulsifier that helps stabilize formulations and improve skin feel.', '1', '2'),
	('CI 77007 / Hydrogen Dimethicone', 'Hydrogen Dimethicone is a silicone derivative widely used in cosmetics for its versatile properties. As a clear and odorless fluid, it serves as an effective emollient and skin-conditioning agent. The chemical formula of Hydrogen Dimethicone is C6H20O2Si3, indicating a modified silicone structure. This ingredient enhances the spreadability of products, imparts a silky texture, and provides a protective barrier on the skin. Commonly found in skincare, haircare, and makeup formulations, Hydrogen Dimethicone contributes to a luxurious feel, facilitates even product application, and helps reduce the greasy feel in cosmetic products, making it a valuable component in various beauty formulations.', '2', '3'),
	('Disodium Phosphate', 'Disodium Phosphate is primarily used as a buffering agent in cosmetics to help maintain the pH of a product. It ensures that the formula remains stable and effective over time.', '1', '2'),
	('Isostearic Acid', 'Isostearic Acid is a fatty acid used in cosmetics and personal care products for its emollient, stabilizing, and conditioning properties. It forms a barrier on the skin to prevent dryness and provide a smooth feel. It also stabilizes emulsions by preventing the separation of oil and water phases in cosmetic formulations. This helps improve the texture and consistency of products like creams, lotions, and sunscreens. In its raw form, Isostearic Acid appears as a colorless to pale yellow liquid with a faint odor and smooth texture. Being compatible with both oil-based and water-based formulations, this ingredient can be found in a variety of products.', '1', null),
	('Lens Esculenta (Lentil) Seed Extract', 'Lens Esculenta (Lentil) Seed Extract is a plant-derived ingredient known for its antioxidant and anti-aging properties. It helps to improve skin texture, promote hydration, and protect the skin from environmental damage, making it a common addition in products targeting dull or aging skin.', '1', '2'),
	('Hydrogenated Phosphatidylcholine', 'Phosphatidylcholine Higher than 50% purity from Soy Lecithin processed Hydrogenation For use in encapsulating ingredients (Phospholipid Encapsulation) to increase absorption increase solubility or increase the stability of the substance', '1', '2'),
	('PEG-30 Phytosterol', 'PEG-30 Phytosterol is a plant-derived emulsifier used in skincare products to improve texture and moisture retention. It helps blend products smoothly and enhances hydration while supporting the skin''s barrier function.', '2', null),
	('Ceramide NG', 'One of the 9 types of ceramides that can be found naturally in the upper layer of the skin. Ceramides make up a big part (about 50%) of the goopy stuff that''s between our skin cells (called extracellular matrix) and play a super important role in having a healthy skin barrier and keeping the skin hydrated.', '1', '2'),
	('C12-13 Alkyl Glyceryl (Hyalorepair)', 'An extra low molecular weight hyaluronic acid that has been alkylated so that it can have a barrier function with both hydrophobic and hydrophilic aspects for skin care. It is a moisturizing and anti-aging agent with sun care concept. It repairs and recovers the barrier which helps the skin to retain moisture. It is derived from a non-animal source and is a biotechnology & fermentation technology product.', '9', '3'),
	('C12-15 Pareth-12', 'C12-15 Pareth-12 is a surfactant and emulsifier used in skincare products to help dissolve oils and improve the spreadability of formulations. It also helps stabilize emulsions, making products feel smoother and more uniform on the skin.', '2', '3'),
	('Snail Secretion Filtrate', 'A component of many beauty products, snail secretion filtrate is made from the slime that snails secrete. The skin is said to benefit from this filtrate in a variety of ways, including hydration, smoothness, and plumpness. Additionally, it''s believed that snail secretion filtrate can lessen the appearance of acne scars, fine lines, and wrinkles. It is a complex mixture of proteoglycans, glycosaminoglycans, glycoprotein enzymes, hyaluronic acid, copper peptides, antimicrobial peptides, and trace elements including copper, zinc, and iron, and is usually obtained from the garden snail, Cornu aspersum. Snail slime cosmetics have recently gained popularity in the United States and are originally a Korean beauty trend.', '1', null),
	('Diglycerin', 'Diglycerin is an excellent moisturizer and humectant that is highly valued in the cosmetic and personal care industry. It effectively attracts moisture, enhancing hydration in products like moisturizers, cleansers, and serums. As a solvent and viscosity modifier, it improves texture and stability in formulations. In its raw form, it appears as a colorless to pale yellow viscous liquid and has a mild, natural scent. Diglycerin is generally recognized as safe for all skin types, being non-irritating and non-sensitizing. Since it is derived from natural sources, it is biodegradable and aligns with eco-friendly and sustainable cosmetics.', '1', '2'),
	('PEG-6 Caprylic/Capric Glycerides', 'PEG-6 caprylic/capric glycerides is a polyethylene glycol (PEG) derivative of a mixture of mono-, di-, and triglycerides of caprylic and capric acids having an average of 6 moles of ethylene oxide. It is a water-loving, thin, and transparent liquid that is soluble in aqueous surfactant solutions can solubilize oils and oil-soluble ingredients and has a nice skin feel. It is a popular ingredient in micellar cleansing waters. It is an excellent emollient and a skin-replenishing component.', '2', '3'),
	('Bakuchiol', 'Bakuchiol is a potent antioxidant and anti-aging ingredient used in a wide variety of cosmetics and skin care products. It has the unique ability to treat skin discoloration caused by environmental exposure. Further, this ingredient fights the visible signs of aging such as wrinkles, and gives a youthful glow to the skin. Bakuchiol is better than retinol as it does not cause any side effects even though it may produce slower results. Additionally, it is great for sensitive skin types and can be used by pregnant women without worries. The Indian name of Bakuchiol is bakuchi or babchi.', '1', '2'),
	('Bacillus/Soybean Ferment Extract', 'Bacillus/Soybean Ferment Extract is a bio-fermented ingredient derived from soybeans using Bacillus bacteria. It is known for its skin-conditioning properties, helping to improve hydration, promote a smoother complexion, and support skin barrier function. The fermentation process enhances the bioavailability of nutrients, making it more effective for skincare. It is often used in anti-aging and moisturizing products.', '1', null),
	('Lactobacillus/Rye Flour Ferment', 'Lactobacillus rye flour ferment is a non-living probiotic made by fermenting rye flour with the microorganism Lactobacillus that’s used to create sourdough bread. In cosmetics, it works as a humectant to draw and hold moisture to skin, helps to balance the natural flora that populate skin’s surface, aids in visibly repairing skin’s barrier, improves signs of dry skin conditions, and can have a calming action. As probiotic Lactobacillus rye flour ferment breaks down on skin, it creates lactic acid, a postbiotic ingredient with many benefits for skin.', '1', null),
	('Lactobacillus/Soymilk Ferment Filtrate', 'Lactobacillus/Soymilk Ferment Filtrate is a fermented soymilk extract processed with Lactobacillus bacteria. It enhances skin hydration, supports the skin barrier, and provides antioxidant benefits. Fermentation increases the bioavailability of nutrients, making it a nourishing and soothing ingredient commonly used in anti-aging and moisturizing skincare products.', '1', null),
	('Fd&C Green No. 3 (Ci 42053)', 'CI 42053 is a cosmetic colorant used for the purpose of enhancing the look of the product or for the embellishment of skin and hair. It is synthetic in nature and can be found in various cosmetic and personal care products such as soaps, shampoos, lotions, and makeup. CI 42053 is also known as Fast green FCF or Green 3 and appears as a greenish blue powder in its raw form.', '6', '2'),
	('Epilobium Fleischeri Flower/Leaf/Stem Extract', 'Epilobium Fleischeri Flower/Leaf/Stem Extract is known for its potent anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. It helps soothe the skin, reducing redness and irritation, and supports the skin barrier by providing essential nutrients.', '1', null),
	('C15-19 Alkane', 'C15-19 Alkane is a lightweight ingredient that is used in a range of cosmetic ingredients because of its many beneficial properties. It is primarily an emollient that renders the skin smooth and soft after application. The benefits of C15-19 Alkane are very similar to the ones offered by mineral oils and silicones. Thus it can also be used as a replacement. This ingredient helps disperse UV filters such as zinc oxide and titanium dioxide.', '3', '3'),
	('Hydrogenated Vegetable Glycerides', 'Hydrogenated vegetable glyceride citrate can be considered a fatty acid salt so; it can be useful in both oil and water. Thus, it can be used in emulsions as an emulsifier. Higher fat content helps penetration to skin and improves smoothness and softness of the skin. It can also be used as surfactant since a surfactant can bind with grease, dirt which can be carried away with the help of water. It can also be best used for dry skin because it moisturizes skin without any irritation due to higher fat content. It is used for body care, skincare and in anti-aging preparations', '1', null),
	('Polyacrylamide', 'Polyacrylamide in facial skincare products functions as a film-forming agent, texture enhancer, and thickener. It helps create a smooth, lightweight feel, improves product spreadability, and provides a soft finish on the skin. While generally considered safe, some formulations limit its use due to potential concerns over acrylamide residues.', '6', '3'),
	('C13-14 Isoparaffin', 'C13-14 Isoparaffin is a commonly used ingredient in skin care and hair care products due to its solvent properties that provide texture to the formulations. It is generally obtained from petroleum sources and appears as a clear, colorless liquid with a lightweight texture. C13-14 Isoparaffin is great for enabling the even distribution of other ingredients in a formulation and forming a balanced product that is easy to spread and feels silky smooth. Further, it is also used to enhance the stability of products and reduce moisture loss from the skin. It is important to note that C13-14 Isoparaffin is not a paraben.', '1', '4'),
	('Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice Powder', 'Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice Powder is the concentrated form of juice derived from aloe vera. It is a potent moisturizing and soothing agent with excellent anti-inflammatory properties. It is rich in good-for-the-skin polysaccharides, vitamins, minerals, enzymes, and amino acids. Due to its water-retentive properties, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice Powder is highly hydrating, and suitable for all skin types, especially dry and sensitive skin. In its raw form, it appears as a fine, off-white to light tan powder with a soft texture that is easily soluble in water - forming a gel-like consistency. Its neutral appearance and mild, sometimes earthy scent make it easy to incorporate into cosmetic formulations without altering the visual or olfactory characteristics of the final product.', '1', '2'),
	('Laureth-7', 'Laureth-7 is a derivative of lauryl alcohol (a fatty alcohol derived from coconut oil). Its chemical formula is C26H54O8. It is used as an emulsifier, texture enhancer, cleanser, surfactant in personal care formulations.', '2', '2'),
	('Polygonum Cuspidatum Root Extract', 'Polygonum Cuspidatum Root Extract is a plant-derived ingredient rich in resveratrol, known for its antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and skin-soothing properties. It helps protect the skin from environmental stressors, reduces redness, and supports an even skin tone, making it beneficial for anti-aging and sensitive skin formulations.', '1', '2'),
	('Ammonium Acryloyldimethyltaurate/VP Copolymer', 'Ammonium acryloyldimethyltaurate/VP copolymer is used as gelling agent for aqueous systems and texturizer, thickener for oil-in-water emulsions. It is used to make glossy well spreadable and fast to absorb emulsions. The elegant O/W emulsions are characterized by dry tack free aesthetic feel. It stabilizes water-insoluble liquids sucb as oils without using additional emulsifiers.', '1', null),
	('Scutellaria Baicalensis Root Extract', 'Scutellaria Baicalensis Root Extract is a potent botanical ingredient renowned for its antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and skin-brightening properties. Rich in flavonoids, particularly baicalin, it helps protect the skin against environmental stressors and UV damage while soothing irritation and reducing redness. Moreover, Scutellaria Baicalensis Root Extract aids in inhibiting melanin production, making it effective in brightening dark spots and promoting a more even skin tone. It is commonly found in serums, creams, and spot treatments, targeting various skin concerns.', '1', '3'),
	('Saccharide Isomerate', 'Saccharide Isomerate is a plant-derived humectant known for its excellent moisture-binding properties. It helps improve skin hydration by attracting and retaining moisture, making it beneficial for dry or dehydrated skin. It provides long-lasting hydration and enhances the skin’s barrier function, reducing water loss. Often used in facial skincare products like moisturizers, serums, and masks for smoother, more supple skin.', '1', null),
	('Acetyl Tetrapeptide-11', 'Acetyl Tetrapeptide-11 is a bioactive peptide used in skincare to improve skin firmness, elasticity, and texture. It helps support the skin’s structural proteins, promoting a smoother and more youthful appearance. Often found in anti-aging and skin-rejuvenating formulations.', '1', null),
	('Acetyl Tetrapeptide-9', 'Acetyl Tetrapeptide-9 is composed of four amino acids, including an acetylated amino acid residue. Acetylation usually helps to improve the stability and bioavailability of the peptide chain. Introduction to the mechanism of Acetyl Tetrapeptide-9: Stimulates the synthesis of basement membrane proteins and collagen, comprehensively rebuilds the skin matrix, and improves epidermal thickness and firmness:', '1', null),
	('Chlorhexidine Digluconate', 'Chlorhexidine digluconate, also known as clorexidina or chlorhexidine gluconate solution, is a commonly used ingredient in cosmetic and personal care products like skin cleansers. It appears in the form of white crystalline powder and has a slightly bitter taste, but it is mostly odorless. Chlorhexidine digluconate is well known for its antibacterial and antifungal properties. It is effective against a wide range of microorganisms, including those that cause skin infections.', '4', '2'),
	('Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7', 'Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, a synthetic peptide, is a key ingredient in anti-aging formulations. It has collagen-boosting properties that target wrinkles and fine lines. It also helps restore the skin’s firmness and elasticity by supporting the skin’s structural components, leading to a firmer and more youthful appearance. Further, this peptide is known for its anti-inflammatory and hydrating benefits. In its raw form, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7 appears as a white to off-white powder and does not affect the texture or appearance of a formulation. Since it is odorless, it is often used in fragrance-free products targeting sensitive skin. This ingredient is commonly found in anti-aging creams and serums, eye creams, and moisturizers.', '1', null),
	('Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1', 'Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1 is widely used in cosmetics for its ability to stimulate collagen production, promote skin healing, and improve the overall appearance of the skin. This synthetic peptide contains three amino acids - glycine, histidine, and lysine - and a fatty acid that are good for the skin and increase the stability of a formulation. When added to skin care products, this ingredient aids in smoother and firmer skin over time while also healing and soothing damaged skin. In its raw form, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1 appears as a white to off-white powder that is generally odorless. It is water soluble making it suitable for formulations like serums, creams, and gels.', '1', '2'),
	('CI 17200', 'CI 17200 is a common synthetic colorant that imparts a purple-red color similar to the color of a red beetroot to a product. It is allowed for use as a colorant in multiple cosmetic products. It is permitted for use in colored ingestible drugs, externally applied drugs and cosmetics, mouthwashes, and dentifrices in the United States. CI 17200 is also used in the European Union, Japan, and other countries. It has been approved by the Food and Drugs Administration (FDA) for limited use in cosmetics and is not approved for use in cosmetics that are applied around the eyes.', '5', '3'),
	('Dimethyl Isosorbide', 'Dimethyl Isosorbide is quite an effective ingredient that is used primarily in water-based ingredients to improve their consistency and texture. It is also an amazing emollient that locks moisture on the topmost layers of the surface, preventing dryness and flaking. It appears as a clear transparent liquid that is colorless to slightly yellow in color. Further, Dimethyl Isosorbide improves the penetration of a product and thus its performance. Contrary to common perception, it is not silicone.', '1', '2'),
	('Steareth-20', 'Polyethylene glycol ethers of stearic acid make up the Steareth ingredients (Steareth-2, Steareth-4, Steareth-6, Steareth-7, Steareth-10, Steareth-11, Steareth-13, Steareth-15, and Steareth-20). Steareth-20 primarily functions as a surfactant and emulsifier in cosmetic products and is generally available as a waxy, solid material. It can be used in the creation of personal hygiene products, deodorants, fragrances, skin, eye, and hair products.', '2', '2'),
	('Hydrogenated Polydecene', 'Hydrogenated polydecene is an alkene that acts as an emollient and may have different viscosities from silky-light to satiny-smooth or rich and luxurious. It is a colorless, watery liquid with a pleasant odor. It is naturally found in some plants like Tussilago farfara.', '2', '3'),
	('Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate', 'Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate is a stable derivative of Vitamin C that is soluble in water. It serves as an antioxidant, effectively combating free radicals and protecting the skin from environmental damage such as UV radiation and pollution. Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate also possesses skin brightening properties, aiding in the reduction of hyperpigmentation and promoting an even skin tone. Moreover, it plays a role in collagen synthesis, contributing to skin firmness and elasticity, thus reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles. Its stability and compatibility make this ingredient popular in various skincare formulations.', '1', null),
	('Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil', 'Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil (argan oil), also known as the \'liquid gold of Morocco\', is a miracle ingredient that has changed the world of personal care. It is an amazing emollient that conditions the skin and hair to make them healthier. Moreover, it is also said to have anti-aging properties. In its raw form, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil appears as a clear yellow liquid that is used widely in cosmetic and personal care products.', '1', '3'),
	('Octyldodecanol', 'Octyldodecanol is an odorless and clear fatty acid that is used to improve the texture of cosmetic products. It has amazing solvent properties that bring stability to cosmetic formulations and also gives a really smooth feel to the final product. Apart from cosmetics, it is also used in skin care products due to its emollient and lubricating abilities.', '1', '3'),
	('Hydrogenated Polyisobutene', 'Hydrogenated Polyisobutene is quite multi-functional and is used liberally in the cosmetic industry. This ingredient is basically a synthetic oil that acts as a preservative to increase the shelf life of the products. What’s more, it also gives the skin a glowy and dewy look. Hydrogenated Polyisobutene is an emollient that leaves the surface smooth and soft. Further, being waterproof, it makes the product last longer on the surface that it is applied on.', '1', '2'),
	('Hydrolyzed Candida Saitoana Extract', 'Hydrolyzed Candida Saitoana Extract is a yeast-derived ingredient known for its skin-revitalizing and protective properties. It helps in enhancing the skin''s vitality, reducing signs of fatigue, and improving overall skin health.', '1', null),
	('Hydrolyzed Jojoba Esters', 'Hydrolyzed Jojoba Esters are derived from Jojoba oil and are used widely in cosmetics for their skin conditioning and emollient properties. They mimic the natural oils of the skin, providing moisture and improved skin texture without leaving a greasy feel.', '1', null),
	('Silanediol Salicylate', 'Silanediol Salicylate is a silicone derivative combined with salicylic acid. This ingredient is often used for its anti-inflammatory, keratolytic, and skin-conditioning properties. It can help to gently exfoliate the skin, leading to improved texture and tone.', '1', null),
	('Sodium Acrylate/Acryloyldimethyltaurate/Dimethylacrylamide Crosspolymer', 'This ingredient is primarily used as a film-forming agent. It helps in forming a flexible layer on the skin''s surface, which can enhance the look and feel of the skin. In addition, it improves the texture of cosmetic products providing a smooth and silky finish.', '1', '2'),
	('Polysorbate 60', 'Polysorbate 60 is an emulsifier and surfactant commonly used in cosmetics to blend water and oil-based ingredients. Derived from sorbitol and oleic acid, its chemical formula is C64H126O26. This amber-colored, oily liquid appears as a golden to yellowish clear solution. Polysorbate 60 enhances the stability of various personal care products, such as creams, lotions, and makeup, by preventing ingredient separation. It also improves texture and provides a smooth feel. Widely favored in the industry, Polysorbate 60 ensures homogeneous formulations and acts as a solubilizer for essential oils and fragrances, facilitating their incorporation into water-based products.', '2', '2'),
	('Biosaccharide Gum-1', 'This ingredient is primarily used as a film-forming agent. It helps in forming a flexible layer on the skin''s surface, which can enhance the look and feel of the skin. In addition, it improves the texture of cosmetic products providing a smooth and silky finish.', '1', '2'),
	('Solanum Lycopersicum (Tomato) Fruit Extract', 'Solanum Lycopersicum Fruit Extract, commonly known as tomato extract, is rich in antioxidants such as lycopene, vitamins A, C, and E. It helps protect the skin from environmental damage, promotes even skin tone, and enhances skin texture. It has anti-inflammatory properties that can reduce redness and it provides hydration for a supple and vibrant skin.', '1', '3'),
	('Ascorbyl Methylsilanol Pectinate', 'Ascorbyl Methylsilanol Pectinate is a stabilized derivative of Vitamin C, known for its antioxidant properties. It aids in brightening the skin tone, restoring firmness, and improving overall skin vitality.', '1', null),
	('Lactic Acid/Glycolic Acid Copolymer', 'Lactic Acid/Glycolic Acid Copolymer is a combination of two alpha hydroxy acids (AHAs) that is often used in skincare formulations for its exfoliating properties. This copolymer helps in gently removing dead skin cells, improving skin texture, tone, and overall complexion.', '1', null),
	('Polyvinyl Alcohol', 'Polyvinyl alcohol is a widely accepted ingredient in the cosmetic industry due to the various functions it serves. It is primarily a film-forming agent that works best with products requiring a barrier function. Polyvinyl alcohol is also water-soluble and has thickening properties, which improves the texture and feel of formulations. It is commonly found in shampoos, conditioners, and moisturizers. Further, Polyvinyl alcohol works as an emulsifier. Due to its film-forming properties, it prevents moisture loss from the surface of the skin.', '1', '2'),
	('Palmitoyl Sh-Tripeptide-5 Norisoleucyl Sh-Nonapeptide-1', 'This is a synthetic peptide complex known for its powerful anti-aging properties. It helps to stimulate collagen production, providing skin with improved firmness and elasticity. It also aids in reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, promoting an overall youthful and revitalized skin appearance.', '1', '2'),
	('Dipotassium Glycyrrhizinate', 'Dipotassium Glycyrrhizate or Dipotassium Glycyrrhizinate Licorice extract acts to reduce inflammation, reduce allergies, and helps strengthen the skin.', '1', '2'),
	('EDTA', 'EDTA (Ethylenediaminetetraacetic Acid) is primarily used in skincare products as a chelating agent to bind metal ions. This helps to improve the stability and efficacy of the product by preventing metal ions from destabilizing the formulation. While it does not provide direct skin benefits, its role in enhancing the product''s overall effectiveness is crucial.', '2', '3'),
	('Ethyl Macadamiate', 'Ethyl Macadamiate is derived from macadamia nut oil and is an excellent lightweight emollient. It helps to improve skin hydration, providing a smooth and silky feel to the skin without a greasy residue. This ingredient mimics human sebum, making it highly compatible with skin, and is often used to enhance skin barrier function and texture.', '1', null),
	('Ceteareth-20', 'Ceteareth-20 is an emulsifying agent that is found in a range of skin care and hair care products. Its special properties help to keep skin and hair smooth, soft, and supple. Ceteareth-20 appears white in color and is an odorless compound that attracts both oil and water, thus keeping the formulations together and stabilizing them. Additionally, it works well with almost all the other ingredients and is safe for all skin types.', '2', '3'),
	('Ceteareth-12', 'Ceteareth-12 is an ingredient commonly used in cosmetics as an emulsifier, surfactant, and solubilizer. It belongs to the Ceteareth family of compounds, which are derived from the reaction of ethylene oxide with fatty alcohols. Ceteareth-12 is often used in formulations to help blend and stabilize oil and water phases, allowing for the creation of smooth and uniform products. It is frequently found in skincare products, including creams, lotions, and cleansers. Ceteareth-12 may also be combined with other ingredients, such as Centella Asiatica extract, to provide additional benefits for the skin.', '2', '3'),
	('Cetyl Palmitate', 'Cetyl Palmitate is a cosmetic ingredient widely used as an emollient, emulsifier, and thickening agent in skincare and personal care products. In its raw form, this compound appears as a white, waxy solid. Cetyl Palmitate enhances the texture of creams and lotions, imparting a smooth and silky feel to the skin while also helping to stabilize formulations. Its emollient properties contribute to skin hydration by forming a protective barrier that reduces moisture loss. Additionally, it improves the spreadability of products, ensuring even application.', '1', '2'),
	('Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil', 'Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil is one of the miracle ingredients in the world of cosmetics and personal care. Also known as sunflower seed oil, it is rich in fatty acids and vitamin E which makes this ingredient good for hydration and also a potent antioxidant. Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil has a non-greasy texture and is lightweight, making it suitable for all skin types. It can commonly be found in products like serums, lotions, and cosmetics where it provides the skin with a youthful and healthy appearance.', '1', '3'),
	('Acetyl Tetrapeptide-2', 'Acetyl Tetrapeptide-2 is a synthetically derived peptide that boosts the skin''s production of collagen and elastin, contributing to improved skin tone and firmness. It also plays a role in promoting cellular repair and regeneration.', '1', null),
	('Trilaureth-4 Phosphate', 'Trilaureth-4 Phosphate is primarily used as a surfactant and emulsifying agent in cosmetic formulations. It helps to create stable mixtures of oil and water, aiding in the texture and consistency of products. It can enhance the spreadability and delivery of other active ingredients.', '2', null),
	('Ferulic Acid', 'Ferulic Acid is a potent antioxidant and skincare ingredient frequently found in cosmetics and skincare formulations. Derived from plants such as rice bran and oats, this ingredient is typically a colorless to pale yellow crystalline powder. In cosmetics, it shines as a skincare superhero due to its ability to combat free radical damage caused by UV radiation and pollution. When applied topically, Ferulic Acid aids in preventing premature aging, reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, and brightening the complexion. It is often incorporated into serums, creams, and sunscreens, offering a natural shield against environmental stressors.', '2', '3'),
	('Citrus Reticulata Peel Extract', 'Citrus Reticulata Peel Extract, derived from the peel of the mandarin orange, is rich in vitamins, antioxidants, and natural acids. It offers exfoliating properties, helps brighten the skin, and can improve skin texture. The extract also has astringent qualities, which can help reduce oiliness and refine pores.', '1', '3'),
	('Phytosteryl/Octyldodecyl Lauroyl Glutamate', 'Phytosteryl/Octyldodecyl Lauroyl Glutamate is a plant-derived emollient that greatly enhances the skin barrier function, providing deep moisturization and a silky texture. It forms a protective layer on the skin, helping to reduce transepidermal water loss and improve skin softness.', '1', null),
	('Hydrolyzed Rhodophyceae Extract', 'Hydrolyzed Rhodophyceae Extract is derived from red algae and is known for its moisturizing and skin-conditioning properties. It helps to improve skin hydration, strengthen the skin barrier, and provides antioxidant protection.', '1', null),
	('Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea Butter)', 'Sheatree, Butyrospermum parkii, also known as Vitellaria paradoxa, is the source of Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter. When raw, it is ivory in colour and is frequently coloured yellow with palm oil or borutu root. It is used in numerous cosmetic and personal care products, such as bath and cleaning products, eye makeup, lotions and creams, suntan products, lipstick, and hair care products, where it functions as emollients and viscosity controllers.', '1', '2'),
	('PEG-9 Glyceryl Laurate', 'PEG-9 Glyceryl Laurate is an emulsifying agent that helps blend water and oil phases in cosmetic products. It also has some surfactant properties that aid in cleansing and solubilizing other ingredients.', null, null),
	('Dianthus Longicalyx Seed Extract', 'Dianthus Longicalyx Seed Extract is derived from the seeds of the Dianthus longicalyx plant. It is known for its moisturizing, antioxidant, and anti-inflammatory properties, which make it beneficial for skin health.', '1', '2'),
	('Acrylates Copolymer', 'Acrylates copolymer is a name given to synthetic copolymers that contain two or more than two monomers like methacrylic acid, acrylic acid, and one of their esters. It comes in the form of white powder or beads. Acrylates copolymer is a film-forming agent that is used in cosmetic and skin care products. It forms a barrier on the skin and results in a very soft and smooth after feel. Further, acrylates copolymer adds water resistance or waterproof quality to formulations.', '2', '2'),
	('Sodium Cocoyl Glycinate', 'Sodium Cocoyl Glycinate is primarily a surfactant that reduces the surface tension of the formulation and is responsible for softening the skin, and also sometimes hair. As an ingredient, it can come in a solid/powder form, and can also be in the form of a colorless to pale yellow liquid. Sodium Cocoyl Glycinate works to leave the skin and scalp clear and healthy. The most important point in that it is non-irritating and creates a rich creamy lather upon application.', '1', '2'),
	('Cocos Nucifera Oil', 'Cocos Nucifera Oil is a natural ingredient that has many medicinal and moisturizing properties. It is insoluble in water and has a very good shelf life - which makes the products last longer. Additionally, Cocos Nucifera Oil is another name of coconut oil which has taken over the cosmetic industry by storm. Cocos Nucifera Oil has lauric acid that has the ability to improve the texture of skin and hair by providing intense hydration and making them healthy. Therefore, it is good for dry skin and hair types.', '1', '3'),
	('Glycol Distearate', 'Glycol distearate is an opacifier and pearling agent used in cleansing products making them white and glossy. It can also give body to shampoos, creams, and emulsions. It is white to cream-colored waxy solid.', '1', '2'),
	('Imidazolidinyl Urea', 'Imidazolidinyl Urea is a multi-functional ingredient that serves as a preservative, stabilizer, and humectant in cosmetic and personal care formulations. It is highly effective against bacteria, yeast, and mold and prevents their growth in cosmetics - extending the shelf life of products. It also stabilizes formulations and prevents the degradation of active ingredients. Further, this ingredient has moisture-retaining properties that help keep the skin hydrated. In its raw form, Imidazolidinyl Urea appears as a white to off-white crystalline powder and can be easily incorporated into a wide variety of cosmetic products.', '4', '2'),
	('PEG-20 Glyceryl Triisostearate', 'PEG-20 Glyceryl Triisostearate is quite an effective ingredient that is used in cosmetic and personal care products as a surfactant. It can mix oil and water-based components really well to form richly textured products. PEG-20 Glyceryl Triisostearate is also a good cleansing and hydrating agent that works well for all skin types.', '2', '3'),
	('Diisostearyl Malate', 'Diisostearyl malate is an emollient which works to condition the skin in cosmetics and personal care products. It also has surfactant properties. It is an odorless and tasteless ester which provides sheen and gloss to the cosmetic formulation. It is thus a favorite addition to cosmetics like lipsticks, lip gloss, but may also be found in other make-up and beauty products like eye shadow, hair dye, blush and sunscreen.', '1', '2'),
	('Ammonium Lauryl Sulfate', 'Ammonium Lauryl Sulfate is a common surfactant found in many cosmetics and personal care products. It plays a crucial role in these formulations by reducing the surface tension between different substances, allowing them to mix effectively. The chemical formula of Ammonium Lauryl Sulfate is C12HNO4S, and it is derived from lauryl alcohol, making it plant-derived in some cases. This versatile ingredient helps create luxurious lather, enhancing the cleansing and foaming properties of shampoos, body washes, and facial cleansers, providing a pleasant and refreshing experience.', '1', '3'),
	('Bis-PEG/PPG-20/5 PEG/PPG-20/5 Dimethicone', 'Bis-PEG/PPG-20/5 PEG/PPG-20/5 Dimethicone is a silicone emulsifier that enhances texture, spreadability, and stability in skincare products.', '2', null),
	('Argania Spinosa (Argan) Kernel Oil', 'Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil (argan oil), also known as the \'liquid gold of Morocco\', is a miracle ingredient that has changed the world of personal care. It is an amazing emollient that conditions the skin and hair to make them healthier. Moreover, it is also said to have anti-aging properties. In its raw form, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil appears as a clear yellow liquid that is used widely in cosmetic and personal care products.', '1', '3'),
	('C14-22 Alcohols', 'C14-22 Alcohols are fatty alcohols derived from natural fats and oils, often used in cosmetic formulations for their emollient and thickening properties. They help to hydrate the skin, improve texture, and stabilize formulations.', '1', null),
	('C12-20 Alkyl Glucoside', 'C12-20 Alkyl Glucoside is a mild, plant-derived surfactant and emulsifier, often used in skincare and haircare products to help mix oil and water-based ingredients and to provide gentle cleansing action.', '2', '2'),
	('Cetearyl Alcohol', 'Cetearyl alcohol is a mixture of stearyl alcohol and cetyl alcohol forming a waxy, white mixture to be used in cosmetics. This chemical is used to bring smoothness and thickness to the products while also providing hydrating properties. While most alcohols are drying for the skin, cetearyl alcohol traps water and treats skin dryness.', '1', '2'),
	('Hydroxyethylcellulose', 'Hydroxyethylcellulose is a gelling and thickening agent derived from cellulose. It also works as a rheology modifier. It is a key ingredient in the formation of big bubbles as it possesses the ability to dissolve in water but also provide structural strength to the soap bubble.', '1', '3'),
	('Spent Grain Wax', 'Spent Grain Wax is an emollient derived from the by-products of beer production. It is rich in essential fatty acids and sterols, which help to restore the skin''s barrier and provide nourishment.', '1', null),
	('Phytosphingosine', 'Phytosphingosine functions as a skin-identical ingredient, mimicking the natural lipids found in the skin''s outer layer. This aids in reinforcing the skin''s barrier function, enhancing moisture retention, and supporting a resilient complexion. Phytosphingosine is also recognized for its antimicrobial properties, making it beneficial in skincare formulations targeting acne or other skin conditions. As a result, Phytosphingosine is a valuable addition to moisturizers, serums, and anti-aging products, contributing to overall skin health and providing a balanced environment for a radiant and hydrated complexion.', '1', '2'),
	('Hexacarboxymethyl Dipeptide-12', 'Hexacarboxymethyl Dipeptide-12 is a cutting-edge peptide known for its multifunctional properties, including skin brightening, anti-aging, and soothing effects. It promotes collagen synthesis and helps in reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.', '1', '2'),
	('Cyclodextrin', 'Cyclodextrin is an ingredient that works mostly in the background to enhance solubility and stabilize other ingredients in a formulation. It provides a controlled release of active ingredients, prolonging their effects and improving their efficacy. Further, it is also used for its odor-masking and texture-enhancing benefits. In its raw form, Cyclodextrin appears as a white to off-white crystalline powder. Since it is odorless, it becomes suitable for formulations where a neutral smell is essential. This ingredient is popular in the cosmetic industry since it is versatile, water-soluble, and has the ability to form inclusion complexes. It is also good for the environment since it is biodegradable.', '1', '3'),
	('Fullerenes', 'Fullerenes are carbon-based molecules known for their strong antioxidant properties. They help neutralize free radicals, thereby providing protection against environmental damage and reducing signs of aging.', '1', '2'),
	('PVP (Polyvinylpolypyrrolidone)', 'The water-soluble polymer polyvinylpyrrolidone (PVP), also known as polyvidone or povidone, is created from the monomer N-vinylpyrrolidone. PVP can be chosen based on the desired application properties and is offered in a variety of molecular weights and associated viscosities. PVP is a linear polymer that consists of 1-vinyl-2-pyrrolidone monomers, and appears like a faintly yellow solid. It is used in the formulation of a wide range of product types including mascara, eyeliner, hair conditioners, hair sprays, shampoos and other hair care products and it majorly works as a film former, emulsion stabilizer, and hair fixative.', '1', '3'),
	('Cyanocobalamin (Vitamin B12)', 'Cyanocobalamin, also known as Vitamin B12, is essential for skin health. It helps in the production of red blood cells and supports healthy skin by preventing dryness, inflammation, and hyperpigmentation.', '1', '3'),
	('Inulin', 'Inulin is a natural polysaccharide found in many plants. It acts as a prebiotic, feeding the beneficial bacteria on the skin, which helps to maintain a healthy skin microbiome. This can contribute to a stronger skin barrier and better overall skin health.', '1', '2'),
	('Lactic Acid', 'Lactic acid is a miracle ingredient in personal care products that mainly functions as an exfoliator - removing the dead skin cells from the surface and leaving the smooth, soft surface underneath. Lactic acid is also a humectant that draws moisture to the upper layers of the skin and keeps it hydrated. This ingredient is quite beneficial in maintaining healthy looking and youthful skin. Further, lactic acid also helps moisturize and condition the hair shafts to leave them smoother and shinier.', '5', '3'),
	('Glycyrrhiza Uralensis Root Extract', 'Glycyrrhiza Uralensis Root Extract, also known as licorice root extract, is a plant-derived ingredient known for its anti-inflammatory, brightening, and soothing properties. It is commonly used to treat hyperpigmentation and redness, making it a popular ingredient in products designed to even out skin tone and calm irritated skin.', '4', '4'),
	('Camellia Oleifera (Tea Oil Camellia) Leaf Extract', 'Also known as tea seed extract, Camellia Oleifera Leaf Extract is rich in antioxidants and known for its anti-inflammatory and hydrating properties. It helps to protect the skin from environmental damage and supports overall skin health.', '1', '3'),
	('Diglucosyl Gallic Acid', 'Diglucosyl gallic acid is a derivative of gallic acid, known for its powerful antioxidant properties and its ability to visibly brighten the skin. It works by converting into trihydroxy benzoic acid (THBA) upon contact with the skin''s microbiome, which then helps reduce hyperpigmentation and improve skin clarity.', '1', null),
	('Almtoyl Sh-Tripeptide-5 Norisoleucyl Sh-Nonapeptide-1', 'Almitoyl Tripeptide-5 boosts collagen production, improving skin elasticity and reducing wrinkles, while Norisoleucyl Sh-Nonapeptide-1 enhances skin texture and reduces inflammation. Together, they promote firmer, smoother, and more youthful-looking skin.', null, null),
	('Palmitoyl Sh-Octapeptide-24 Amide', 'Palmitoyl SH-Octapeptide-24 Amide is a synthetic peptide designed to mimic natural peptides involved in skin regeneration. It has potential anti-aging benefits and can help in improving the overall appearance of the skin.', null, null),
	('Limnanthes Alba (Meadowfoam) Seed Oil', 'Limnanthes Alba Seed Oil, also known as meadowfoam seed oil, is a lightweight, non-greasy oil renowned for its moisturizing properties. It helps to reinforce the skin barrier, providing hydration and preventing moisture loss. Its high content of antioxidants and fatty acids make it a versatile ingredient for both skin conditioning and protection against environmental stressors.', '1', '2'),
	('Dicaprylyl Ether', 'Dicaprylyl ether is an oil derived from caprylic acid and is used to enhance the texture of the ingredient as well as of the skin and hair. Even being an oil, this magic ingredient is non-comedogenic and does not clog pores or cause acne breakouts. Dicaprylyl ether has fast-spreading capabilities and acts as an emollient and a solvent in formulations.', '1', '2'),
	('Polyglyceryl-4 Laurate Sebacate', 'Polyglyceryl-4 Laurate Sebacate is a mild, plant-based emulsifier that helps blend water and oil phases in cosmetic formulations. It enhances the spreadability and texture of skincare products while maintaining skin''s moisture balance. It is commonly used in creams, lotions, and serums for its non-greasy feel and moisturizing properties.', '1', '2'),
	('Leontopodium Alpinum Callus Culture Extract', 'Leontopodium Alpinum Callus Culture Extract, commonly known as Edelweiss extract, is derived from the Edelweiss flower. It is rich in antioxidants and offers protection against environmental stressors. This ingredient also boasts anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, making it a highly beneficial addition to skincare formulations.', '1', null),
	('Polyglyceryl-6 Caprylate/Caprate', 'Polyglyceryl-6 Caprylate/Caprate is a plant-derived surfactant and emulsifier that helps to stabilize and blend the oil and water phases in cosmetic formulations. It also has mild skin-conditioning properties.', '1', null),
	('Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Extract', 'Cucumis Sativus Extract, derived from cucumber, is a popular ingredient in cosmetics for its hydrating and soothing properties. It appears as a clear to light green liquid with a fresh cucumber scent. This extract is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, that help protect the skin from environmental damage and maintain a healthy complexion. It is also used to refresh and revitalize tired skin, reduce puffiness, and provide a cooling effect. Cucumis Sativus Extract is a natural and safe ingredient that is suitable for all skin and hair types.', '1', '3'),
	('Sorbic Acid', 'Sorbic Acid is a natural organic compound used primarily as a preservative in cosmetic formulations. It helps prevent the growth of mold, yeast, and fungi, ensuring product safety and longevity.', '2', '3'),
	('Haematococcus Pluvialis Oil', 'Haematococcus Pluvialis Oil is a rich source of astaxanthin, a powerful antioxidant known for its ability to neutralize free radicals, protect the skin from UV damage, and improve overall skin health. It also provides anti-inflammatory benefits.', '1', '2'),
	('Astaxanthin', 'Astaxanthin is a powerful antioxidant derived from microalgae. It helps to protect the skin from environmental damage, improve skin elasticity, and reduce signs of aging.', '1', '2'),
